Nine suspects in the Solai Dam tragedy were released on Monday on Sh5 million bond each, with sureties of the same amounts. They were granted the alternative of Sh2.5 million cash bail each. The suspects were ordered to surrender their passports to the court ahead of the pre-trial conference on August 3. The suspect include include the owner of Patel Farm Perry Manusukh. They spent the weekend at Naivasha Medium Security Prison. The nine people were charged with 48 counts of manslaughter following the May dam collapse that left at least 48 people dead. Read:Â Patel Dam owner charged with causing Solai deaths Also read: Solai Dam tragedy: Billionaire Patel to spend weekend in cells Click here for the latest political news